f2494cb3-8b15-4864-a60c-89ef8e900a26.13e74780-f181-4a41-858c-90d0b0b3ace9.description=
This operation waits for the number of seconds specified in the "seconds" input.

Inputs\:
    seconds - The number of seconds to wait.

Results\:
    resultString – This is the primary output. It contains the "completed sleep" message if the operation completed successfully and an error message otherwise. 

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
f2494cb3-8b15-4864-a60c-89ef8e900a26.2f19e39f-39fc-4456-85cd-8b8a705938d6.description=
This operation checks whether a string matches another string, using a specific matching rule. The "toMatch" input is the string that is checked for matching the "matchTo" expression. 

Inputs\:
    matchType - The type of match to perform.
Valid values\: Exact Match, Contains, Contains Once, Does Not Contain, Match All Words, Match No Words, Regex (The values are not case sensitive)
Default value\: Exact Match
    toMatch - The string that is checked for matching.
    matchTo - The string to match against.
Example\: If "matchType" is “RegEx”, the "matchTo" input is a regular expression such as\: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. 
    ignoreCase - Specifies whether to ignore case when matching or not.
Valid values\: False, True
Default value\: False

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the string "Matches" if the "toMatch" string matches the "matchTo" string. Otherwise, it contains the string "Does Not Match".  

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

f2494cb3-8b15-4864-a60c-89ef8e900a26.4a63159b-0548-4657-9622-cbeeca4606b4.description=
Retrieves information about a guest os running in a virtual machine. VM tools must be running on the guest to retrieve this information.

Inputs\:
    host - VMware vCenter, ESX or ESXi host hostname or IP.
    user - VMware username.
    password - VMware user's password.
    port - Port to connect on.
Examples\: 443, 80
    protocol - Connection protocol.
Valid values\: "https", "http"
    closeSession - Close the internally kept VMware Infrastructure API session at completion of operation.
    vmIdentifierType - Virtual machine identifier type 
Valid values\: "inventorypath", "name", "ip", "hostname", "uuid", "vmid"
    virtualMachine - Primary Virtual Machine identifier. Inventorypath (Datacenter/vm/Folder/MyVM), Name of VM, IP (IPv4 or IPv6 depending upon ESX version), hostname (full), UUID, or the VM id (vm-123,123).
    vmDatacenter - Virtual machine's datacenter.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed successfully.
    failure - Something went wrong.

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output.  Descriptive result of the operation.  Reason for error on failure.
    state - Running state of the guest operating system.   Possible values\: running, shuttingdown, resetting, standby, notrunning, unknown
    hostname - Hostname of the guest according to the guest operating system.
    ipAddress - Primary IP address of the guest according to the guest operating system.  Example value\: 10.11.22.33
    guestOsId - Guest operating system identifier (short name).  Example value\: "windows7Server64Guest"
    guestOsDescription - Guest operating system full name.  Example value\: "Microsoft Windows Server 2008 R2 (64-bit)"
    guestFamily - Guest operating system family.  Example value\: "WindowsGuest "
    guestNicInfo - A json array of json objects describing the network interfaces of the guest.  Each json object has three keys\: 
macaddress - Mac address of the guest nic.  Example value\: 00\:50\:56\:87\:01\:93
ipAddresses - A json array of ip addresses assigned to the nic.  Example value\: ["fe80\:\:9802\:e33\:4e2\:2caf%15","16.93.30.83"]
network - The name of the network port group the nic is attached to.
    guestDiskInfo - A json array of json objects describing the disks attached to the guest.  Each json object has three keys\:
diskPath - The mount point of the disk on the guest.  Example value\: "C\:\"
capacity - Size of the disk in bytes.
freespace - Amount of freespace on the disk in bytes. 

Notes\:
Inventory Path Formatting\: If host is an ESX server inventory path will be\: ha-datacenter/vm/ .  If host is a vCenter the inventory path will be\: /vm// . The / part of the path is based on the "Virtual Machines & Templates" view in the vCenter client. The inventory path is case sensitive.
f2494cb3-8b15-4864-a60c-89ef8e900a26.592dbc22-8b72-421b-beb1-e2f73686445a.description=
Attempts to reboot the guest virtual machine.

Inputs\:
host - VMWare host hostname or IP.
user - VMWare username.
password - VMWare user's password.
port - Port to connect on.
protocol - Connection protocol (http or https).
closeSession - Close the internally kept VMWare Infrastructure API session at completion of operation (true, false).
virtualMachine - Primary Virtual Machine identifier. Inventorypath (Datacenter/vm/Folder/MyVM), Name of VM, IP (IPv4 or IPv6 depending upon ESX version), hostname (full), UUID, or the VM id (vm-123,123).
vmIdentifierType - Virtual machine identifier type (inventorypath, name, ip, hostname, uuid, vmid).

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
returnResult - Operation result message.

Notes\:
Inventory Path Formatting\: If host is an ESX server inventory path will be\: ha-datacenter/vm/ .  If host is a vCenter the inventory path will be\: /vm// . The / part of the path is based on the "Virtual Machines & Templates" view in the vCenter client. The inventory path is case sensitive.

f2494cb3-8b15-4864-a60c-89ef8e900a26.9f397479-b745-46ff-8f81-27af96ad6446.description=Counts from one number to another number. 
Inputs\:
from - The number to start counting at.
to - The number to count to.
incrementBy - The number to increment by while counting. If unspecified this is 1. If you wanted to count 2,4,6,8 this would be 2.
reset - If true, then the counter will restart counting from the beginning.

NOTE\: These values must be between -9223372036854775808 and 9223372036854775807

Returns\:
The number that was just counted.

Note\: the primary result is resultString, Result can also be used. result (All lower case) should not be used as it is the response code.

Responses\:
has more - Not yet done counting.
no more - Done counting. This will only be returned once, then counting restarts.
failure - Something went wrong.
